---
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Section from "~/components/Section.astro";
import Container from "~/components/Container.astro";
import Heading from "~/components/Heading.astro";
import Article from "~/components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout>
	<Section class:list={"theme-section-alt"}>
		<Container>
			<Heading>
				<h1 slot="heading-title" class="h2 theme-heading">Corporate Social Responsibility</h1>
				<p slot="heading-content">
					Events that do good — for your people, your community, and the world around us.
				</p>
			</Heading>

			<Article>
				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Our Commitment</h2>
				<p>
					At ABM Partners, we believe that how you run an event says as much about your organisation as
					the event itself. Corporate social responsibility is not a checkbox for us — it is embedded
					in the way we plan, source, and deliver every engagement. We help our clients use their events
					as a platform to demonstrate genuine values and make a measurable positive impact.
				</p>

				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Sustainable Event Practices</h2>
				<p>
					We work with venues, caterers, and suppliers who share our commitment to environmental
					responsibility. From minimising single-use plastics and reducing food waste to selecting
					venues with strong sustainability credentials, we actively look for ways to lower the
					environmental footprint of every event we manage. For clients with specific sustainability
					targets, we can provide detailed reporting on waste, emissions, and resource consumption.
				</p>

				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Community and Social Impact</h2>
				<p>
					Many of our clients choose to incorporate a community element into their events — whether
					that is a charity auction, a volunteering day attached to a conference, or donating surplus
					catering to local organisations. We have strong relationships with community partners across
					Australia and can help you identify and embed meaningful social impact activities that
					resonate with your audience and align with your company's values.
				</p>

				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Inclusive and Accessible Events</h2>
				<p>
					Great events welcome everyone. We design our programs with accessibility and inclusion at the
					forefront — ensuring venues are physically accessible, materials are available in appropriate
					formats, and the event experience is welcoming to attendees of all backgrounds and
					abilities. We also actively support diverse speaker and facilitator representation across our
					programs.
				</p>

				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Responsible Supply Chain</h2>
				<p>
					We carefully vet the suppliers and partners we work with, giving preference to businesses
					that demonstrate ethical labour practices, local sourcing, and a commitment to reducing their
					environmental impact. When you work with ABM Partners, you can be confident that your event
					spend is supporting a responsible supply chain.
				</p>

				<h2 class="font-bold theme-heading h3">Work With Us</h2>
				<p>
					If you want to make your next event not just memorable, but meaningful, we would love to
					talk. <a href="/virtual-roundtables" class="theme-link">Get in touch</a> with our team to discuss
					how we can build a CSR strategy into your event from the ground up.
				</p>
			</Article>
		</Container>
	</Section>
</Layout>
